text: San Gavino Monreale (Santu 'Èngiu) is a town and comune (municipality) in the Province of Sud Sardegna in Sardinia, Italy. As of 2016, 8,671 people lived there. Its area is 87.4 km². It is 54 meters above sea level. == References == == Other websites == Category:Communes of the Province of South Sardinia
title: San Gavino Monreale
